						               													<description>A family-friendly party card game with simple rules &amp;amp; reversal elements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Here we are is cat caf&amp;eacute; which is topic of the street. You are the staff of this shop. Cats are relaxing around. When the time goes by slowly, one of the staff whispered, &amp;quot;Who is most liked by them?&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You do everything to the cats. Of course, to be the most favorite of the cats in this shop.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;--from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round, the staff of this cat caf&amp;eacute; must try and guess what the cat is going to want from them. You'll know which of the four cat decks is going to be drawn from next, and if you've been paying attention, you should have an idea of the cards left in that deck. You'll play one of your four prediction cards, and either gain or lose the cat's favorability.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But be careful which prediction card you play, because you only have one of each! You can play your 'Leave Me Alone' card to avoid losing favorability, and to return all your cards back to your hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You also have a 'Full Power' card you can use when you're really confident in your prediction. If you guessed right, you can get a favorability bonus - either +5, +15, x3, or even x4 - depending on where you are on the scoring track. But the 'Full Power' card has to rest for a while before it can be used again, so choose wisely!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The staff member who the cats like best wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
